## Why this is the correct test now

The controller should not decide whether the content is French, Dutch, or another language. It now sends message keys to the Thymeleaf template, and Spring resolves them according to the active locale.

Your template should therefore use expressions like:

```html
<title th:text="#{${pageTitleKey}}"></title>

<h1 th:text="#{${titleKey}}"></h1>

<p th:text="#{${messageKey}}"></p>

<strong th:text="#{${strongMessageKey}}"></strong>
```

So the responsibilities are now:

```text
Controller test:
checks the correct translation keys

Message bundle:
contains the translated text

Template:
resolves the key using the current locale
```

The two failing tests shown in the terminal are therefore fixed by updating the assertions, not by changing `ErrorController`.
